  "prompt": "What is the difference between chocolate and truffles?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between chocolate and truffles:\n\nChocolate:\n1. A broad category of sweet food made from cocoa beans\n2. Comes in various forms like bars, chips, or blocks\n3. Can be milk, dark, or white\n4. Processed from cocoa beans and often contains sugar and other ingredients\n5. Eaten directly as a confection or used in baking\n\nTruffles:\n1. A type of chocolate confection\n2. A small, round chocolate treat usually filled with ganache, cream, or other flavored centers\n3. Often coated in cocoa powder, nuts, or chocolate\n4. More complex and typically more expensive than regular chocolate\n5. Usually handmade and considered a gourmet dessert\n\nNote: There's also a culinary meaning of \"truffle\" referring to a rare, expensive fungus found underground, which is different from chocolate truffles.\n\nIn summary, truffles are a specific type of chocolate confection, while chocolate is a broader category of food product.",
